HEADWORD: Protoörganism
<hw>Pro`to*⟦oum⟧r"gan*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Proto-</ets> + <ets>organism</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>An organism whose nature is so difficult to determine that it might
be referred to either the animal or the vegetable kingdom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

